Description: Low rectangular wooden box, painted black, with a flat lid. Lid made of 5 joined pieces with one piece missing from the corner. Edge of lid and one side of box have two attached knobs for sealing with cord. Contains four linen-wrapped mummified ducks with joints of meat.
Curator's comments: J H Taylor, 'The Burial Assemblage of Henutmehyt: inventory, date and provenance', in W V Davies (ed), Studies in Egyptian Antiquities. A tribute to T G H James (BMOP 123) (London, 1999), 59, 63, 64, 67, pl. 21.
Associated places: Associated with: Thebes (historic - Upper Egypt) (used at)
